<subSubSection pageId="58" pageNumber="59" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="58.[151,1437,872,2015]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,324,980,1007]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Dorsum with Dc-2 fused to an unpaired medial plate (
<figureCitation box="[933,1035,981,1007]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="60.[151,250,1772,1797]" captionTargetBox="[151,1433,337,1740]" captionTargetId="figure@60.[151,1436,337,1752]" captionTargetPageId="60" captionText="FIGURE 28. Family Teratothyadidae. a.–d., Teratothyasides ravenala, female; a. genital field and surrounding sclerites (MD 175); b. chelicera (MD 028); c. gnathosoma with palp and chelicera (MD 175); d. palp medial (MD 187); e.–i., Teratothyasides heptaplax; e.–f. male (MD 154); e. dorsum, f. genital field, partial view; g.–i. female; g. gnathosoma with right palp, lateral (MD 154); h. chelicera (MD 165); i. left palp lateral (MD 154, P-1 lacking)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613358" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613358/files/figure.png" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Fig. 28 e</figureCitation>
). Genital field with roundish, rather short Ac-1 (L 30–48, 23–27 % flap L) and rather large Ac-2 (L 75–90, 40–50 % flap L–see 
<figureCitation box="[1180,1280,1017,1044]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="60.[151,250,1772,1797]" captionTargetBox="[151,1433,337,1740]" captionTargetId="figure@60.[151,1436,337,1752]" captionTargetPageId="60" captionText="FIGURE 28. Family Teratothyadidae. a.–d., Teratothyasides ravenala, female; a. genital field and surrounding sclerites (MD 175); b. chelicera (MD 028); c. gnathosoma with palp and chelicera (MD 175); d. palp medial (MD 187); e.–i., Teratothyasides heptaplax; e.–f. male (MD 154); e. dorsum, f. genital field, partial view; g.–i. female; g. gnathosoma with right palp, lateral (MD 154); h. chelicera (MD 165); i. left palp lateral (MD 154, P-1 lacking)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613358" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613358/files/figure.png" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Fig. 28 f</figureCitation>
). Mouth parts (
<figureCitation box="[160,240,1053,1079]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="60.[151,250,1772,1797]" captionTargetBox="[151,1433,337,1740]" captionTargetId="figure@60.[151,1436,337,1752]" captionTargetPageId="60" captionText="FIGURE 28. Family Teratothyadidae. a.–d., Teratothyasides ravenala, female; a. genital field and surrounding sclerites (MD 175); b. chelicera (MD 028); c. gnathosoma with palp and chelicera (MD 175); d. palp medial (MD 187); e.–i., Teratothyasides heptaplax; e.–f. male (MD 154); e. dorsum, f. genital field, partial view; g.–i. female; g. gnathosoma with right palp, lateral (MD 154); h. chelicera (MD 165); i. left palp lateral (MD 154, P-1 lacking)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613358" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613358/files/figure.png" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
g–i) stout (L/H chelicera 5.1–5.6; P-3, 1.0–1.2, P-4, 2.7–3.0).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="59" lastPageNumber="60" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="58.[151,1437,872,2015]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,347,1088,1115]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Description:</emphasis>
Membranous integument with rounded papillae. Sclerite plates with relatively few, large, angular pores (6–10 along an imaginary transect crossing dorsocentral plates–see 
<figureCitation box="[985,1089,1125,1151]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="60.[151,250,1772,1797]" captionTargetBox="[151,1433,337,1740]" captionTargetId="figure@60.[151,1436,337,1752]" captionTargetPageId="60" captionText="FIGURE 28. Family Teratothyadidae. a.–d., Teratothyasides ravenala, female; a. genital field and surrounding sclerites (MD 175); b. chelicera (MD 028); c. gnathosoma with palp and chelicera (MD 175); d. palp medial (MD 187); e.–i., Teratothyasides heptaplax; e.–f. male (MD 154); e. dorsum, f. genital field, partial view; g.–i. female; g. gnathosoma with right palp, lateral (MD 154); h. chelicera (MD 165); i. left palp lateral (MD 154, P-1 lacking)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613358" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613358/files/figure.png" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Fig. 28 e</figureCitation>
). Genital field with three pairs of acetabula, basal sclerite of Ac-1 fused to medial genital flap margin, but posteriorly with an indentation indicating area of fusion (
<figureCitation box="[364,465,1197,1224]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="60.[151,250,1772,1797]" captionTargetBox="[151,1433,337,1740]" captionTargetId="figure@60.[151,1436,337,1752]" captionTargetPageId="60" captionText="FIGURE 28. Family Teratothyadidae. a.–d., Teratothyasides ravenala, female; a. genital field and surrounding sclerites (MD 175); b. chelicera (MD 028); c. gnathosoma with palp and chelicera (MD 175); d. palp medial (MD 187); e.–i., Teratothyasides heptaplax; e.–f. male (MD 154); e. dorsum, f. genital field, partial view; g.–i. female; g. gnathosoma with right palp, lateral (MD 154); h. chelicera (MD 165); i. left palp lateral (MD 154, P-1 lacking)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613358" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613358/files/figure.png" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Fig. 28 f</figureCitation>
). Each genital plate with 20–25 (10–15 medial, about 10 posterior) setae, the posterior setae rather strong and stiff. Leg claws proximoventrally with a very flat projection. Gnathosoma (
<figureCitation box="[1261,1364,1233,1259]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="60.[151,250,1772,1797]" captionTargetBox="[151,1433,337,1740]" captionTargetId="figure@60.[151,1436,337,1752]" captionTargetPageId="60" captionText="FIGURE 28. Family Teratothyadidae. a.–d., Teratothyasides ravenala, female; a. genital field and surrounding sclerites (MD 175); b. chelicera (MD 028); c. gnathosoma with palp and chelicera (MD 175); d. palp medial (MD 187); e.–i., Teratothyasides heptaplax; e.–f. male (MD 154); e. dorsum, f. genital field, partial view; g.–i. female; g. gnathosoma with right palp, lateral (MD 154); h. chelicera (MD 165); i. left palp lateral (MD 154, P-1 lacking)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613358" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613358/files/figure.png" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[1314,1364,1233,1259]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="2.8" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" unit="g" value="28.0">28 g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
) short and robust, in lateral view rostrum distinctly set off from base. Chelicera (
<figureCitation box="[976,1078,1269,1296]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="60.[151,250,1772,1797]" captionTargetBox="[151,1433,337,1740]" captionTargetId="figure@60.[151,1436,337,1752]" captionTargetPageId="60" captionText="FIGURE 28. Family Teratothyadidae. a.–d., Teratothyasides ravenala, female; a. genital field and surrounding sclerites (MD 175); b. chelicera (MD 028); c. gnathosoma with palp and chelicera (MD 175); d. palp medial (MD 187); e.–i., Teratothyasides heptaplax; e.–f. male (MD 154); e. dorsum, f. genital field, partial view; g.–i. female; g. gnathosoma with right palp, lateral (MD 154); h. chelicera (MD 165); i. left palp lateral (MD 154, P-1 lacking)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613358" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613358/files/figure.png" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Fig. 28 h</figureCitation>
) stout and relatively short, claw strong, as long as, in one specimen distinctly longer than, basal segment. Palp (
<figureCitation box="[1037,1160,1305,1332]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="60.[151,250,1772,1797]" captionTargetBox="[151,1433,337,1740]" captionTargetId="figure@60.[151,1436,337,1752]" captionTargetPageId="60" captionText="FIGURE 28. Family Teratothyadidae. a.–d., Teratothyasides ravenala, female; a. genital field and surrounding sclerites (MD 175); b. chelicera (MD 028); c. gnathosoma with palp and chelicera (MD 175); d. palp medial (MD 187); e.–i., Teratothyasides heptaplax; e.–f. male (MD 154); e. dorsum, f. genital field, partial view; g.–i. female; g. gnathosoma with right palp, lateral (MD 154); h. chelicera (MD 165); i. left palp lateral (MD 154, P-1 lacking)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613358" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613358/files/figure.png" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[1089,1140,1305,1331]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="2.8" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" unit="g" value="28.0">28 g</quantity>
, i
</figureCitation>
) stout; P-1 with a dorsal seta in distal third; P-2 ventral margin slightly concave, the two strong setae shifted to mediodistal margin, dorsally with four setae; P-3 and -4 shortened, P-3 with a lateral seta in proximal half and two dorsal setae, P-4 maximum H in centre, distally strongly narrowed, ventral margin bowed, one dorsal seta in proximal quarter, near distal margin with three hair-like setae ventrally, dorsally and medially, mediodistal seta fine and pointed, on a prominent projection; P-5 long and slender (14–16 % total L), with three setae (proximal, dorsodistal, ventro distal) and three long, slender claws.
</paragraph>
